article.headline: Georgia St. 85, Jacksonville St. 78
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Michael Moynihan had 16 points and led five players in double-digits as Georgia State rallied from a 14-point second-half deficit to defeat Jacksonville State 85-78 on Saturday night. Georgia State (8-19) outscored the Gamecocks (6-21) 45-28 in the second half by shooting 58 percent from the field. Leonard Mendez scored 15 points on five 3-pointers, Kevin Lott had 13 and a game-high seven rebounds, Ousman Krubally scored 12 points and Deven Dickerson added 10. Jonathan Toles scored a career-high for 23 points for the Gamecocks. DeAndre Bray scored 15 points, Jeremy Bynum followed with 11 and Will Ginn added 10. Moynihan hit a 3-pointer that put the Panthers ahead 73-67 with four minutes to play, then made six straight free throws down the stretch. He was 8-for-10 from the line on the night. Jacksonville State led 50-40 at the half and extended its lead to 59-45 early in the second before Georgia State went on a 17-4 run to pull within one at 63-62 at the 12-minute mark. Lott put the Panthers ahead for good, 68-66, with a pair of free throws with 5:54 left.
